# Google OAuth Configuration
# Get these from Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com

# For Desktop (Web Application credentials)
# Add "http://localhost" to authorized redirect URIs
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_desktop_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_desktop_client_secret

# For Android, you'll need separate credentials:
# 1. Create Android type OAuth credentials
# 2. Add your app's package name (e.g., com.chamlang.app)
# 3. Add SHA-1 certificate fingerprint
#    - Debug: keytool -list -v -keystore ~/.android/debug.keystore -alias androiddebugkey -storepass android -keypass android
#    - Release: Use your release keystore
# 4. Use the Android client ID in your build (handled automatically by the plugin)

# Required API scopes (automatically requested):
# - openid
# - email
# - profile
# - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.file

# How to get OAuth credentials:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com
# 2. Create a new project or select existing one
# 3. Enable "Google Drive API"
# 4. Go to "Credentials" → "Create Credentials" → "OAuth 2.0 Client ID"
# 5. For Desktop: Choose "Web application"
#    - Add "http://localhost" to authorized redirect URIs
# 6. For Android: Choose "Android"
#    - Add package name and SHA-1 fingerprint
# 7. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret to this file
